<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Trawma Siirjen on 04-24-2001 04:13 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I will definately agree that there has been somewhat of a decline in human compassion in EQ (mirroring RL.)

BUT

Uber lewts give a player/guild more freedom.  Freedom to go to zones where they are more likely to die than without the uber lewt - freedom to do certain zones as a guild with minimal downtime (cleric epic comes to mind.)

Since LEWT is a key ingredient in how powerful your character/guild is, it only stands to reason that UBER LEWT will be fought over.  Afterall, lewt makes EQ more fun, not only for lewt ho's, but gives more flexibility even for a casual roleplayer who is not focused on lewt.  More options make EQ more fun.

My cleric can't even visit Sebilis because she doesn't have the key.  This is a prime example of how LEWT matters.

The Celestial Healing scroll made me a much better cleric.  Another great example of important lewt.  Having that scroll makes the game more fun for me.

Competition also makes the game fun.  I do not believe that "might makes right", but I think that a little dose of reality makes EQ a bit more "real", which is nice.  Sure, it's a fantasy world, but it ain't Utopia, and I'm glad.

I don't care one lick if the uber guilds are roleplaying, but they certainly ARE playing a role.  The role they play makes perfect sense to me.  You are small, they are powerful.  They are taking what they can from Norrath.  If you are trampled upon, it's because you are standing in the way of their fun.

People do take this game seriously.  I'd say that sitting at your PC bored out of your skull for days on end is taking the game way too seriously.

Breaking down the walls with an army, killing everything in sight, and kill stealing Ragefire from the guy sitting there camping it for days is completely the opposite.  This method makes a lot more sense to me, sounds like A LOT more fun, and shows who is too serious (spawn campers), and who knows how to have fun.

Fun at the expense of others?  Perhaps.  But we are all anonymous, and no one really gets hurt anyways.  Like we all say, tis just a game.  In real life, most of us would not act that way, but this is not real life, so do whatever the hell you want.

You dis me on my server, though, and I will have you hunted down and killed repeatedly.  > :)

Trawma Siirjen
48 High Elf
United Legions
Vallon Zek</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
